orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_7664aaecf8de97cc5f1b8115d3b8d234" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_40469ec0b2b59faa3604378255b757de" parent="aspace_7664aaecf8de97cc5f1b8115d3b8d234" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_6c68e27d010695f5de97c50791168b48" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_687d57fb1e600d62e0203cb09fc5e19b" parent="aspace_6c68e27d010695f5de97c50791168b48" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_2acc2c1ce4dcff4b8a78652468af6f4d" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1f703fed34be714543f83d15de37c8b2" parent="aspace_2acc2c1ce4dcff4b8a78652468af6f4d" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-